<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The for statement initializes both the loop counter (j) and another object (io) in the first clause, and increments both j and io in the third clause. Clause 1 requires the first clause to only set or define the loop counter; Clause 3 requires the third clause to modify only the loop counter. Having io assigned and incremented in the for header therefore violates Rule 14.2 (clauses 1 and 3).
</scenario>
